<Author>Crestfallen
<Content>Overpriced and Overused My family and I stayed at the Sofitel for 4 nights. We booked in January for a September stay, but this obviously did not get us a priority room with a view, just the brick walls of an opposite facing building.Upon arrival the bellmen were very attentitive. Our bags were brought up to our rooms and we were given instructions on how to use the rooms amenities (although it seemed more like a ploy to get a tip to me).The foyer and facade of the hotel were beautiful....but that's where it ends.My room was worn. The carpet had stains everywhere (as did the carpet in the second room that was booked). The furniture was beat up, the air conditioner was broke, and the shower had.....BLACK MILDEW! I did not take my shoes off the entire time in my room, nor did I touch anything in the shower.Housekeeping was just ok....and by this, I mean, while you could tell they came to your room because the bed was made, they did little else. They left 1 bottle of water at the bedside every night (but both rooms had 2 occupants....and after a long day of walking, I think everyone would appreciate a bottle of water) . We did not utilize room service or our minibar due to the high prices .We asked for a wake up call that never came our first night.There is hardly any space to unpack but for a tiny closet with 5 hangers and 2 tiny shelves, so plan on living out of your suitcase.Now, the pluses..location, location, location. 1 block away from the subway, and 2 blocks from Old Ebbitt Grill, which we ate at 3 times in 4 days, and was truly one of the highlights of our trip...do not miss!The hotel bar was nice, and we sat outside and had very attentive service and complimentary snacks.We paid $380 for the first night, $320 the second night and $210 the last 2 nights, and, all in all, this place is not worth the money. While it is a short walk to all the attractions, we took the subway 75% of our stay, so no matter where you stay, you can always take the subway.The restaurant rarely had anyone dining any of the 4 days we stayed, so we figured this was a sign.Save your money and stay somewhere else. 
