<Author>Mme_X
<Content>Very nice room and convenient location Good-sized room and spacious bathroom on the third floor were nicely decorated in sleek-but-comfy decor. The room was quiet enough, even though it faced a busy street (but we stayed on a weekend, when there is less traffic.) Spotless housekeeping. Other amenities include a robe, nice toiletries, separate bath tub and shower. I saw no problem with the hairdryer (unlike a previous poster.) The cocktail lounge looked very inviting, but we were in town for a wedding and those events precluded a stop in (but we'd gladly do it next time we're in town!) There is no coffee maker in the room, but very good complimentary coffee and tea are served in the bar in the morning, i.e. better than what usually comes out of a hotel guestroom pot. The staff and concierge were friendly and helpful throughout.The location is near Lafayette Park, i.e. vicinity of the White House, and not a far walk to the mall and its museums. It is also close to some good restaurant options, like the historic-but-renovated Ebbets Grill on the next block.Some downsides: while the dining room is probably very good, the breakfasts are pricey -- even a continental will cost $15; eggs slightly more; buffet slightly more. This is not unusual for Washington, but you have to want an extensive breakfast to make it worth it for you. However, there is a Starbucks and a more moderate diner close by (but the latter is closed on weekends.) The restaurant comes well recommended for dinner, but our wedding events occuppied our time.Another downside: this hotel is with the trend of using a duvet/comforter instead of a sheet and bedspread/blanket. While there are decor and hygiene reasons for this, I don't find it as comfortable as having the option of just a light sheet covering us at night. The result: you have to crank up the air conditioning to be comfortable with this all-or-nothing warm duvet. At other hotels, we've asked to have the bed changed to sheet-and-blanket/coverlet option, but we just let it go this time. A sheet and duvent would have made us more comfortable.To sum: we'd be happy to stay here again, but we were also happy that we got a good price for the room on Travelocity. ...but this place is definitely worth considering! 
