<Content>As good as the other reviews say My partner and I visited DC for a leisure trip, and chose the Sofitel based on reviews here, and also on good experiences with other Sofitels. We spent 5 nights there, and fully endorse all the other positive reviews.The service stands out above everything else: unfailingly courteous and friendly, we were made to feel at home and were accommodated throughout -- of note was being allowed a quite late check out (3pm) without the slightest problem.The (superior grade) room was comfortable, and room service and laundry were reliable. The bathroom was of excellent standard, with high quality Roger  Gallet toiletries. All in, it was of the excellent standard we've come to expect of Sofitel, and we'd return to this one without any doubt.A couple of slight downsides: the gym was extremely small and we wouldn't recommend using it. And the restaurant in the hotel seems to be about the only quality place in the vicinity to have breakfast, which typically came in around $45 per day for two all in (inc tax and service). We were offered a deal on arrival where, for $50 a day for the two of us, we could have been upgraded to a deluxe room and had breakfast thrown in; in our jet-lagged state, for some reason we turned down that deal, and in retrospect we should have gone for that.However, all in this is an excellent hotel, and highly recommended. 
